    <p><a href="https://blisk.io/">Blisk</a> is the new kid on the block to help web developers getting things done right. Blisk is a web browser that has three frames on its interface the left frame display a range of Mobile device that you can choose. The middle frame display how a given website will look like on the chosen device (the left frame) and the right frame displays the website as you could  see it in your day-to-day browser like Firefox or Chrome. For sure Firefox and Google Chrome offers many addons or extensions that front-end dev can toggle to view how the website will look like in an Iphone but you have to toggle or to enable those addons/extensions. By default Blisk come with similar extension already enable.
</p>
